
[1]chondrodite

   CHONDRODITE, n. A mineral, called also Brucite. It occurs in grains or
   imperfect crystals, or in four-sided prisms with rhombic bases,
   truncated on the two acute lateral edges. It is translucent; and its
   color varies from reddish or amber yellow to grayish brown.
